<PostLayout title="A Grudge" date="September 12, 2022" category="Blackout Poetry" description="Newspaper blackout poetry by Ryan Kopperud. Words revealed by redacting the page around them — work, frenzy, and the quiet rebellion of a grudge." type="poetry">

<img src="/images/blackout-a-grudge.webp" alt="Blackout poetry: A Grudge — words revealed from a blacked-out newspaper page" loading="lazy" class="w-full max-w-md mx-auto mb-10 rounded-sm shadow-lg" />

<p>work frenzied<br />
dawn 'til dusk.<br />
clocking in,<br />
I think I'll make<br />
me efforts to be useful<br />
a grudge.</p>

